      <div class="msgContentFrame">*rank 20 GLA*  <br /> <br />after partying a couple nights in cassiopa hollow rank 20-23 6 person and hearing the feedback from other party members as to how much skill gains they were getting, it was clear to my that my sword skill was not even remotely close to the gains they were recieving. the DD classes and casters were saying they were getting fairly constant 400-500 skill ups each crab, and i would be getting between 150-250.  <br /> <br />1) is the GLA 500 cap skill gain split between shield and sword gains?  <br />2) is using phalanx as much as possible key to getting comparable skill gains to the other party members?  <br />3) is it possible on a single mob to get more than 500 skill points in total, after adding up all the &quot;mini&quot; skills gains you see from individual attacks?  <br /> <br /> <br />on a side note, the pugilist in my group was constantly taunting and was apparently getting good skill gains from doing so .. i found this to be quite annoying, but if he was getting skill ups i couldnt very well ask him to stop. anyone care to comment on that also?</div>
