      <div class="msgContentFrame">The only time you gain skill when being hit is when you parry.  You will only gain weapon skill on a parry.  The Parry animation looks just like a shield block animation though. <br /> <br />You can not gain shield skill when guard is not active. I've never gotten a shield skillup on Aegis, but I only use it on emergencies. <br /> <br />Had a 6 hour party yesterday on Efts.  I was the tank.  I did not use guard at all. Only used Aegis on panic HP moments. At the end of the party I had gained 0 shield skill. <br /> <br />I haven't gained more then 1k Shield skill since I hit Rank 14 Sentinel only because I never use guard outside of soloing leves. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />Super Ninja Edit: Now that the cold meds are wearing off and I'm thinking clearer, Aurelius is correct that you -can- gain both shield and sword skill while being hit, however it's under certain conditions such as parry and shield block. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 25th 2010  2:45pm by Dreadnotfl </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXI(Seraph): Dreadnot <br /> <br />FFXIV (Selbina) Seraphic Dreadnought <br /> <br />Gladiator Rank 27 <br />Blacksmith Rank 25</div></div>
