      <div class="msgContentFrame">It seems to me that SE took a page from the FFXI book regarding skill gains as it plays similar to skill ups in campaign. Meaning that skill gains are tied to the number of different skills you use and the amount of damage you do. When I first started I went with a vit build thinking that if I do less damage it would be fine because I'd just have more chances to gain skills. At around 20-22 I started to get an average of 57 skill per fight on mobs regardless of what they con'd. I ended up switching the a dex build and immediately, the same exact mobs where giving 150-200 sword and skill. I even noticed that shield bash became a major contributor to shield skill ups, so far 178 off a single shield bash. Also I am not completely certain that shield and sword skills share a cap because I believe I have gotten combination that totaled more then 500. So if you're have low skill ups try capping dex using the (rank*2)+32 estimate and see if that changes anything. Hope this helps some of you out there.  </div>
